Ace Turbo implementation audit against `task.md`

Status summary

- Not all features in `task.md` are fully implemented yet.
- The persistence layer has moved forward substantially: users, orders, turbos, vehicle records, lookup logs, and IP blocks now go through a Prisma-first repository with safe local fallback when live infrastructure is not configured.
- The remaining work is now much narrower and more UI/infrastructure focused than before.

Implemented well enough to count as present

- Real persistent shopping cart
- Real Stripe checkout and webhook fulfilment, when Stripe env vars are configured
- Order confirmation emails and invoice PDFs
- User registration, login, order history, and invoice downloads
- Protected B2B trade pricing
- Contact form and click-to-call
- Basic news/blog system
- Lookup logging
- Rate limiting on core mutation endpoints
- Competitor resource protection through signed protected exports and login walls
- GA4 and GTM hooks
- Schema.org product markup on product pages
- Redis-backed cache/session hooks when Redis is configured
- eBay Trading API submission flow when eBay credentials are configured
- Prisma-first runtime access for users, turbos, orders, vehicles, lookup logs, and IP blocks when `DATABASE_URL` is real and Prisma client is generated
- Backend turbo filtering for make, model, year, engine, BHP, and part number
- Real rotating homepage hero carousel using `swiper`
- Admin SEO link generation UI from live turbo records
- Admin eBay listing creation UI with draft/submission history
- Lookup stats panel component wired into the admin stats dashboard
- Tracked auth sessions with revocation-aware validation and admin session inventory controls
- XML sitemap route generated from live turbo and blog content
- Product detail pages upgraded with structured specs, multi-image galleries, fitment notes, and workshop guidance
- Account self-service session/device management
- Middleware-side session-status check before protected pages continue

Still missing or only partially implemented

1. Product pages are materially richer, but still not fully migrated
- Product pages now include richer specs, multiple local gallery assets, workshop notes, OEM references, and fuller technical sections.
- They still need real legacy catalog content imported at scale instead of seeded/derived content for only part of the range.

2. Admin CRUD is still partial, but the core management flows are now live
- Turbo create, edit, and delete now work from the admin UI.
- Order status updates now work from the admin UI.
- User role changes and IP block create/remove now work from the admin UI.
- SEO link generation now works from the admin UI.
- eBay listing creation now works from the admin UI.
- Session inventory and revoke actions now work from the admin UI.
- Turbo validation summaries and management stats are now live.
- Order and user panels now include richer reporting/detail context.
- Still missing:
  - deeper cross-entity reporting screens
  - more advanced bulk operations and audit trails

3. User/session management is improved, but still not complete
- Session tracking and invalidation are now implemented.
- Admins can view and revoke individual sessions or all sessions for a user.
- Customers can now view and revoke their own sessions from the account area.
- Middleware now checks current session status before protected requests continue.
- Still missing:
  - deeper device fingerprinting beyond parsed user agent and IP
  - richer session audit detail and export/reporting

4. DOMPurify server-side sanitisation is only partially complete
- Shared sanitisation now has a DOMPurify-backed path and is wired into rich-text server handling.
- The current workspace does not yet have `jsdom` installed, so the server path safely falls back to plain-text sanitisation until dependencies are refreshed.

5. External security audit is not actually run
- Audit scheduling/tracking exists.
- No real Pentest Tools or Sucuri scan has been executed from this repo flow.

6. HTTPS everywhere is not fully implemented in deploy infrastructure
- App headers and docs are present.
- Actual Cloudflare/Vercel HTTPS enforcement depends on deployment configuration outside the repo.

7. Google AdSense / AdWords ready placement zones are still missing
- Analytics hooks exist.
- Explicit ad placement zones and ad-ready layout surfaces have not been implemented.

8. Cloudflare integration is partial
- IP block sync helper exists.
- Full CDN/WAF/analytics/rules management is not implemented end to end in the app.

9. Existing data migration is only scaffolded
- A migration script/report exists.
- It does not yet import real legacy Ace Turbo data into Prisma/MySQL or the runtime store.

10. Production persistence still depends on real infrastructure setup
- The Prisma-first repository is in place.
- Live MySQL persistence still requires:
  - valid `DATABASE_URL`
  - `prisma generate`
  - database migrations applied
  - production deployment wired to the real database

11. Full production Redis-backed behavior is still conditional
- Redis support exists and is used when configured.
- The app still falls back to local in-process/file behavior in development, so production-only Redis semantics are not guaranteed unless infra is present.

